ZH: 燕子是夏季常见的候鸟。
EN: Swallows are common migratory birds in the summer.
ZH: 燕子通常筑巢在高处的悬崖上。
EN: Swallows usually build their nests on high cliffs.
ZH: 燕子的巢由泥土和唾液构成。
EN: Swallows' nests are made of mud and saliva.
ZH: 燕子每年春天返回它们的繁殖地。
EN: Swallows return to their breeding grounds every spring.
ZH: 我喜欢在家门口观察燕子的飞翔。
EN: I enjoy observing the swallows' flight right outside my door.
ZH: 我家附近有一对燕子在筑巢。
EN: There's a pair of swallows building a nest near my house.
ZH: 燕子的飞行速度非常快，几乎难以捉摸。
EN: Swallows fly extremely fast, almost hard to catch.
ZH: 燕子用它们的嘴巧妙地捕捉飞虫。
EN: Swallows skillfully catch flying insects with their beaks.
ZH: 燕子的叫声清脆悦耳。
EN: Swallows have a clear and melodious chirping sound.
ZH: 燕子是中国文化中的吉祥象征。
EN: Swallows are a symbol of good fortune in Chinese culture.
ZH: 我家的屋檐上常年有一群燕子栖息。
EN: A group of swallows always nests on the eaves of my house year-round.
ZH: 燕子的展翅高飞令人赞叹不已。
EN: It's awe-inspiring to watch swallows spread their wings and soar high.
ZH: 孩子们总是兴奋地指着天空中飞过的燕子。
EN: Children always excitedly point at the swallows flying across the sky.
ZH: 燕子的智商在鸟类中相对较高。
EN: Swallows have relatively high intelligence among birds.
ZH: 燕子是居住在开阔地区的鸟类。
EN: Swallows are birds that inhabit open areas.
ZH: 燕子的迁徙距离可以达到几千公里。
EN: Swallows can migrate distances of several thousand kilometers.
ZH: 我们的院子里有一个燕子窝，里面是一窝小燕子。
EN: There's a swallow's nest in our yard, and inside are several baby swallows.
ZH: 每天早晨我喜欢听燕子的歌声。
EN: I enjoy listening to the swallows' song every morning.
ZH: 家乡的农田里总是可以看到燕子飞翔。
EN: Swallows can always be seen flying in the fields of my hometown.
ZH: 燕子是人们心目中的自由飞翔的化身。
EN: Swallows are the embodiment of freedom and flight in people's hearts.
